<poem>
    <metadata>
            <first_line>Four Trees - upon a solitary Acre -</first_line>
            <date period="middle">1863</date>
            <poem_number>J742</poem_number>
            <source>https://www.edickinson.org/editions/2/image_sets/12170725</source>
            <recipient>none</recipient>
            <poem_themes>nature, solitude</poem_themes>
    </metadata>
    
    <body>
        <stanza> 
            <line>Four Trees - upon a solitary Acre -</line>
            <line>Without Design</line>
            <line>Or Order, or Apparent <variant>signal</variant> -  <variant>notice</variant> Action -</line>
            <line>Do <variant>reign</variant> - <variant>hinder</variant> - Maintain -</line>
        </stanza>
        
        <stanza>
            <line>The Sun - upon a Morning meets them -</line>
            <line>The Wind -</line>
            <line>No nearer Neighbor - have they -</line>
            <line>But God -</line>
        </stanza>
        
        <stanza>
            <line>The Acre gives them - Place -</line>
            <line>They - Him - Attention of Passer by -</line>
            <line>Of Shadow, or of Squirrel, haply -</line>
            <line>Or Boy -</line>
        </stanza>
        
        <stanza>
            <line>What Deed <variant>they bear</variant> is Their's unto the General Nature -</line>
            <line>What Plan</line>
            <line>They severally -  <variant>promote - or</variant> retard - or further -</line>
            <line>Unknown -</line>
        </stanza>
    </body>
</poem>
